ğŸŒ Access the API

API Base URL:

http://127.0.0.1:8000


Swagger UI (interactive docs):

http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs


ReDoc:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/redoc

ğŸ“Œ API Endpoints
ğŸ”¹ Health Check
GET /

ğŸ”¹ Get all hosts
GET /all

ğŸ”¹ Get host by hostname
GET /host/{hostname}


Example

/host/Host1

ğŸ”¹ Get hosts by cloud provider
GET /cloud/{cloud_name}


Example

/cloud/aws

ğŸ”¹ Get hosts by region
GET /region/{region_name}


Example

/region/us-east-1

ğŸ”¹ Get hosts by status
GET /status/{status}


Example

/status/active
/status/inactive

ğŸ”¹ Get hosts by tag
GET /tag/{tag_key}/{tag_value}


Example

/tag/Environment/Production

ğŸ”¹ Get host by private IP
GET /private_ip/{private_ip}


Example

/private_ip/192.168.1.1

ğŸ”¹ Get host by public IP
GET /public_ip/{public_ip}


Example

/public_ip/1.1.1.1

âŒ Error Handling

If no matching host is found, the API returns:

{
  "detail": "No hosts found for the specified criteria"
}


With appropriate HTTP status codes like 404.

ğŸ§  Design Notes

Case-insensitive search for cloud, region, tags

Inventory is loaded once at startup for performance

Uses Path() for parameter validation and documentation

Uses HTTPException for clean error handling

ğŸš€ Future Improvements

Add POST / PUT / DELETE endpoints (CRUD)

Persist inventory in a database

Add authentication (JWT)

Convert responses to Pydantic models

Add query-based filtering (?cloud=aws&region=us-east-1)

